Behavior definition:
- Wraps each existing input line independently; existing `\n` boundaries are preserved.
- Breaks on whitespace when possible.
- If a single word exceeds `maxWidth`, it is split into fixed-size chunks.
- Leading whitespace at the start of a wrapped line is discarded.
- Internal spaces are preserved only when they fit on the current line.
- Trailing spaces are removed from emitted lines.
- `maxWidth` must be a positive integer.

