A hash table stores key-value pairs by computing an index from each key with a hash function, so lookup, insert, and delete are usually **O(1)** on average.

- **Hash function**: turns a key into an integer.
- **Buckets**: the table is an array of slots/buckets.
- **Collision**: two keys map to the same bucket.
- **Separate chaining**: each bucket holds a small list of entries; collisions are stored in that list.
- **Resizing**: when the table gets too full, rebuild into a larger bucket array to keep operations fast.

With **string keys**, the hash function usually combines character codes into a number. With **separate chaining**, insert and lookup work by:
1. Hash the key.
2. Convert hash to bucket index with `% bucketCount`.
3. Walk that bucket’s chain to find or update the entry.

Here’s a simple implementation in JavaScript for **string keys** and **integer values**:

```js
class HashMap {
  constructor(initialCapacity = 16) {
    this.buckets = Array.from({ length: initialCapacity }, () => []);
    this.size = 0;
    this.loadFactor = 0.75;
  }

  _hash(key) {
    let hash = 0;
    for (let i = 0; i < key.length; i++) {
      hash = (hash * 31 + key.charCodeAt(i)) >>> 0;
    }
    return hash;
  }

  _bucketIndex(key) {
    return this._hash(key) % this.buckets.length;
  }

  _resize() {
    const oldBuckets = this.buckets;
    this.buckets = Array.from({ length: oldBuckets.length * 2 }, () => []);
    this.size = 0;

    for (const bucket of oldBuckets) {
      for (const [key, value] of bucket) {
        this.set(key, value);
      }
    }
  }

  set(key, value) {
    if (typeof key !== 'string') {
      throw new TypeError('Key must be a string');
    }
    if (!Number.isInteger(value)) {
      throw new TypeError('Value must be an integer');
    }

    const index = this._bucketIndex(key);
    const bucket = this.buckets[index];

    for (const entry of bucket) {
      if (entry[0] === key) {
        entry[1] = value;
        return;
      }
    }

    bucket.push([key, value]);
    this.size++;

    if (this.size / this.buckets.length > this.loadFactor) {
      this._resize();
    }
  }

  get(key) {
    const index = this._bucketIndex(key);
    const bucket = this.buckets[index];

    for (const [entryKey, value] of bucket) {
      if (entryKey === key) {
        return value;
      }
    }

    return undefined;
  }

  has(key) {
    return this.get(key) !== undefined;
  }

  delete(key) {
    const index = this._bucketIndex(key);
    const bucket = this.buckets[index];

    for (let i = 0; i < bucket.length; i++) {
      if (bucket[i][0] === key) {
        bucket.splice(i, 1);
        this.size--;
        return true;
      }
    }

    return false;
  }
}

// Example
const map = new HashMap();
map.set('apple', 3);
map.set('banana', 7);
map.set('apple', 10);

console.log(map.get('apple'));  // 10
console.log(map.get('banana')); // 7
console.log(map.has('pear'));   // false
console.log(map.delete('banana')); // true
console.log(map.get('banana')); // undefined
```

