A semaphore limits how many threads can access a shared resource at the same time. It keeps a permit count: acquiring a permit decrements the count, and releasing one increments it. If no permits are available, additional threads wait until one is released.

In your case, a semaphore with **3 permits** allows at most **3 concurrent users** of the resource pool.

```java
import java.util.concurrent.ExecutorService;
import java.util.concurrent.Executors;
import java.util.concurrent.Semaphore;
import java.util.concurrent.TimeUnit;

public class ResourcePoolExample {
    private static final int MAX_CONCURRENT_USERS = 3;
    private final Semaphore semaphore = new Semaphore(MAX_CONCURRENT_USERS);

    public void useResource(int workerId) {
        try {
            semaphore.acquire();
            System.out.println("Worker " + workerId + " acquired a resource. Available permits: " + semaphore.availablePermits());

            Thread.sleep(2000);

            System.out.println("Worker " + workerId + " releasing resource.");
        } catch (InterruptedException e) {
            Thread.currentThread().interrupt();
            System.out.println("Worker " + workerId + " was interrupted.");
        } finally {
            semaphore.release();
            System.out.println("Worker " + workerId + " released a resource. Available permits: " + semaphore.availablePermits());
        }
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) throws InterruptedException {
        ResourcePoolExample pool = new ResourcePoolExample();
        ExecutorService executor = Executors.newFixedThreadPool(6);

        for (int i = 1; i <= 6; i++) {
            int workerId = i;
            executor.submit(() -> pool.useResource(workerId));
        }

        executor.shutdown();
        executor.awaitTermination(10, TimeUnit.SECONDS);
    }
}
```

### How it works
- `new Semaphore(3)` creates 3 permits.
- `acquire()` blocks when all 3 permits are in use.
- `release()` returns the permit so another waiting thread can proceed.
- With 6 workers, only 3 run inside the critical section at once.

