serializeFormData({
  name: '',
  active: false,
  tags: ['a', 'b'],
  meta: { count: 2, note: null },
  'filter[status]': 'open',
  duplicate: ['x', 'x']
});
// name=&active=false&tags%5B%5D=a&tags%5B%5D=b&meta%5Bcount%5D=2&meta%5Bnote%5D=&filter%5Bstatus%5D=open&duplicate%5B%5D=x&duplicate%5B%5D=x
```

Behavior:
- arrays become repeated `key[]=` entries
- empty strings stay empty
- `null` serializes as an empty value
- booleans become `true` / `false`
- duplicate keys are preserved by repeated pairs
- literal brackets in keys are preserved because the full key is encoded, so `filter[status]` becomes `filter%5Bstatus%5D`

